DATA CLOUD
Create a Connected App for Query Workspaces

You can use a connected app to connect a query workspace to Data Cloud.

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS
USER PERMISSION SET NEEDED
To create a connected app:	Data Cloud Admin
From Setup, in the Quick Find box, enter Apps, and select App Manager.
Click New Connected App.
Enter the name, API Name, and email address for your connected app.
VALUE	DESCRIPTION
Connected App Name	Query Workspaces.
API Name	

QueryWorkspaces.

We recommend using an API name with no spaces between 'Query' and 'Workspaces'.


Contact Email	Enter your email address.
In the API (Enable OAuth Settings) section, select Enable OAuth Settings.
For Callback URL, enter https://<<orgdomain>>.my.salesforce.com/services/authcallback/QueryWorkspaces and substitute the <<orgdomain>> with the domain name of your org.
The callback URL is same as the OAuth redirect URI. Verify the callback URL after creating an auth provider. It must be same as the authentication provider’s authorized endpoint URL.
Using the arrows, add or remove the OAuth scopes for the connected app.
An OAuth scope defines the permissions for the connected app, which are granted as tokens after the app is authorized.
VALUE	DESCRIPTION
Manage user data via APIs(api)	Allows access to the current, logged-in user’s account using APIs, such as REST API and Bulk API 2.0. This scope also includes chatter_api, which allows access to Connect REST API resources.
Manage user data via Web browsers(web)	Allows access to Data Cloud REST API data. Use this scope to manage profile records.
Perform ANSI SQL queries on Data Cloud (cdp_query_api)	Allows ANSI SQL queries of Data Cloud data on behalf of the user.
Perform requests at any time(refresh_token, offline_token)	

Allows a refresh token to be returned when the requesting client is eligible to receive one. With a refresh token, the app can interact with the user’s data while the user is offline. This token is synonymous with requesting.

refresh_token
Select Require Secret for the Web Server Flow and Require Secret for Refresh Token Flow.
Click Save. Next click Continue.
Under Query Workspaces connected app, click Manage Consumer Details and get the consumer key and consumer secret. They're used in Create an Auth Provider for Query Workspaces.

Syncing a connected app can take up to 5 minutes.

After you configure the connected app, Create an Auth Provider for Query Workspaces. Make sure the callback URL is same as the authentication provider’s authorized endpoint URL.
